<paragraph id="854536D14F47FFCCA5F5F83A685D4B1A" blockId="9.[136,1452,1763,2078]" lastBlockId="10.[136,1452,158,725]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="88" pageId="9" pageNumber="87">
<emphasis id="B78EEAC34F47FFCFA5F5F83A6D714D86" bold="true" box="[189,264,1979,2005]" pageId="9" pageNumber="87">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="42FA4D524F47FFCFA46CF83A6D9E4D86" authorityName="Justo &amp; C. K. Pradeep" authorityYear="2014" box="[292,487,1979,2005]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Pluteus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="9" pageNumber="87" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="padanilus">
<emphasis id="B78EEAC34F47FFCFA46CF83A6D9E4D86" box="[292,487,1979,2005]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="87">Pluteus padanilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by a stipe base with distinct blue or blue-green tinges, broadly ellipsoid to ellipsoid basidiospores (Qm = 1.28), pleurocystidia with truncate to subcapitate apices or with 2–3 indistinct short apical projections and the presence of incrusting parietal pigment at the apex in some pleuro- and cheilocystidia. All species discussed herein differ from 
<taxonomicName id="42FA4D524F44FFCCA48DFF1E6E354AEB" authorityName="Justo &amp; C. K. Pradeep" authorityYear="2014" box="[453,588,158,184]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Pluteus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="padanilus">
<emphasis id="B78EEAC34F44FFCCA48DFF1E6E354AEB" box="[453,588,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">P. padanilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the lack of incrusting parietal pigment at apex of the cystidia. Additionally, 
<taxonomicName id="42FA4D524F44FFCCA5C0FF426D4C4A8F" box="[136,309,194,220]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Pluteus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="glaucotinctus">
<emphasis id="B78EEAC34F44FFCCA5C0FF426D4C4A8F" box="[136,309,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">P. glaucotinctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has few cheilocystidia with brownish pigment and a majority of pleuro- and cheilocystidia with rounded apices and with no apical projections; 
<taxonomicName id="42FA4D524F44FFCCA760FF666EF14B53" authorityName="P. Arrill. &amp; Justo" authorityYear="2014" box="[552,648,231,256]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Pluteus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="izurun">
<emphasis id="B78EEAC34F44FFCCA760FF666EF14B53" box="[552,648,231,256]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">P. izurun</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has longer pileipellis elements (up to 380 μm); 
<taxonomicName id="42FA4D524F44FFCCA1D8FF66694D4B53" authorityName="Menolli &amp; Capelari" authorityYear="2014" box="[1168,1332,230,256]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Pluteus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="meridionalis">
<emphasis id="B78EEAC34F44FFCCA1D8FF66694D4B53" box="[1168,1332,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">P. meridionalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a stipe with no distinct blue-green tinges and narrower basidiospores (Qm = 1.40); and 
<taxonomicName id="42FA4D524F44FFCCA6ACFE8A68334B77" authorityName="Menolli &amp; Minnis" authorityYear="2014" box="[996,1098,266,292]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Pluteus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="thoenii">
<emphasis id="B78EEAC34F44FFCCA6ACFE8A68334B77" box="[996,1098,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">P. thoenii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having preponderantly subglobose basidiospores (Qm = 1.15) and longer cheilocystidia (up to 94 µm long).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="854536D14F44FFCCA5F5FED369414817" blockId="10.[136,1452,158,725]" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">
An additional morphological character that separates 
<taxonomicName id="42FA4D524F44FFCCA655FED26FD14B3F" authorityName="Justo &amp; C. K. Pradeep" authorityYear="2014" box="[797,936,338,364]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Pluteus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="padanilus">
<emphasis id="B78EEAC34F44FFCCA655FED26FD14B3F" box="[797,936,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">P. padanilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the other species in this complex is the presence of clamp-connections at some septa of the hymenophoral trama hyphae. The presence/absence of clampconnections in the pileipellis hyphae is a useful character for the species-level taxonomy of 
<taxonomicName id="42FA4D524F44FFCCA1D8FE1B69004BE7" authority="sect. Pluteus" box="[1168,1401,410,437]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Pluteus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="section" section="Pluteus">
<emphasis id="B78EEAC34F44FFCCA1D8FE1B689D4BE7" box="[1168,1252,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">Pluteus</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="B78EEAC34F44FFCCA06DFE1B69004BE7" box="[1317,1401,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">Pluteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but its presence in other parts of the basidioma is not constant enough to be used as a reliable character (
<bibRefCitation id="E16B4B204F44FFCCA1ABFE3F69D94B8B" author="Justo, A. &amp; Malysheva, E. &amp; Bulyonkova, T. &amp; Vellinga, E. C. &amp; Cobian, G. &amp; Nguyen, N. &amp; Minnis, A. M. &amp; Hibbett, D. S." box="[1251,1440,446,473]" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" pagination="1 - 85" refId="ref7935" refString="Justo, A., Malysheva, E., Bulyonkova, T., Vellinga, E. C., Cobian, G., Nguyen, N., Minnis, A. M. &amp; Hibbett, D. S. (2014) Molecular phylogeny and phylogeography of Holarctic species of Pluteus section Pluteus (Agaricales: Pluteaceae), with description of twelve new species. Phytotaxa 180: 1 - 85. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 180.1.1" type="journal article" year="2014">
Justo 
<emphasis id="B78EEAC34F44FFCCA06DFE3E692F4B8B" box="[1317,1366,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">et al</emphasis>
. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="E16B4B204F44FFCCA5C0FE636DBE4BAF" author="Horak, E. &amp; Heinemann, P." box="[136,455,482,508]" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" refId="ref7648" refString="Horak, E. &amp; Heinemann, P. (1978) Flore illustree des champignons d'Afrique centrale 6: Pluteus &amp; Volvariella (complements). National Botanical Garden of Belgium, Meise." type="book" year="1978">Horak &amp; Heinemann (1978)</bibRefCitation>
also reported the presence of a few clamp-connections on the pileipellis elements in the African collections named as 
<taxonomicName id="42FA4D524F44FFCCA49DFD866EF14873" box="[469,648,518,544]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Pluteus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="glaucotinctus">
<emphasis id="B78EEAC34F44FFCCA49DFD866EF14873" box="[469,648,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">P. glaucotinctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but they were not observed during our re-examination. One should not disregard the fact that clamp connections are often more difficult to find in older, dried herbarium material.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="854536D14F44FFCCA5F5FDCF69204887" blockId="10.[136,1452,158,725]" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">
Recently, 
<bibRefCitation id="E16B4B204F44FFCCA462FDCF6E72483B" author="Menolli Jr, N. &amp; de Meijer, A. A. R. &amp; Capelari, M." box="[298,523,590,616]" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" refId="ref8569" refString="Menolli Jr, N., de Meijer, A. A. R. &amp; Capelari, M. (2014) The genus Pluteus (Pluteaceae, Agaricales) from the state of Parana, Brazil. Nova Hedwigia (in press)." type="book" year="2014">
Menolli 
<emphasis id="B78EEAC34F44FFCCA4CEFDCE6DC5483B" box="[390,444,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">et al.</emphasis>
(2014)
</bibRefCitation>
reported the presence of cheilocystidia with incrusting parietal pigment at the apex in one Brazilian material (coll. ANc-4214) under the name of 
<taxonomicName id="42FA4D524F44FFCCA64EFDF26FCA48DF" box="[774,947,626,652]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Pluteus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="glaucotinctus">
<emphasis id="B78EEAC34F44FFCCA64EFDF26FCA48DF" box="[774,947,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">P. glaucotinctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. According to their description it could fit also within the concept of 
<taxonomicName id="42FA4D524F44FFCCA43DFD166D8548E3" authorityName="Justo &amp; C. K. Pradeep" authorityYear="2014" box="[373,508,662,688]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Pluteus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="padanilus">
<emphasis id="B78EEAC34F44FFCCA43DFD166D8548E3" box="[373,508,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">P. padanilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, further molecular investigation will be necessary to elucidate the identity of the material studied by the authors and to certify the real occurrence of 
<taxonomicName id="42FA4D524F44FFCCA6DBFD3A68384887" box="[915,1089,698,724]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Pluteus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="glaucotinctus">
<emphasis id="B78EEAC34F44FFCCA6DBFD3A68384887" box="[915,1089,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">P. glaucotinctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="42FA4D524F44FFCCA12DFD3A68954887" authorityName="Justo &amp; C. K. Pradeep" authorityYear="2014" box="[1125,1260,698,724]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Pluteus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="padanilus">
<emphasis id="B78EEAC34F44FFCCA12DFD3A68954887" box="[1125,1260,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">P. padanilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="FDED76414F44FFCCA047FD3B692C4887" box="[1295,1365,698,724]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
